<br>
&quot;That's MY level range!&quot;<br>
/gasp<br>
<br>
Well, got into groups and started hunting like a mad woman. Needless to say, experience modifier for Fungus Grove is cranked RIDICULOUSLY high. What makes it even better is that more than 75% of the mobs in the zone are NON-AGGRO. Heck, the Tarmoks and Underbulks don't even cross-aggro/assist!<br>
<br>
SO, being the coniving little mage that I am.. I've started soloing in there and it's wonderful XP (as long as you DD a fair amount, so the pet doesn't do 50% + of combat damage). That usually means 2 Scars and 1 Char on the average Tarmok, and I'm chewing my way through this horrid level.<br>
<br>
Thank the gods I found Fungus Grove!<br>
<br>
Few small tips: Stay away from the 'small mushroom' mobs. They DO cross-assist quite nastily, and will gang up on you like nobody's business. Also the 'Mutant Dreg' mobs drop a 'Fetid Flesh Belt' which is actually fairly nice (coming from someone STILL wearing a Braided Cinch Cord belt). I think Tarmok's and Underbulks are best for teaming up/solo'ing on. Just experiment, and be careful. Best thing is to get into a GROUP in FG before you solo in there. Lets you get the hang of the mobs, faster. <p><center><image src="http://home.houston.rr.com/jtully1/tunisig.jpg"><br><b>Tuni Gearspinner</b><br>
