<br>
Other than that.. at 55 pretty much everything in zone is Blue or Light Blue to you. Just DO NOT... I repeat DO NOT mess with the Deep Cavern Lotus Flowers. They aren't above 50.. but have SILLY amounts of hit points , can DD for upto 500 damage (ouch) AND they summon you. Over all more grief than they're worth.<br>
<br>
But Tarmoks are good. Pull them with Malosi at max spell range.. and back them up a bit, then have your pet intercept. I can usually get them one by one that way. Then I just cast Scirocco once, pet heal, Scirocco again.. and phoooom. Dead Tarmok.<br>
<br>
Good luck. And if you're hunting Shrooms or Mutants.. get into a group for it. +) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxerath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xerath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/01 2:45:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=135.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Fungus Grove!</span><hr size=1> What I love about this zone is the entrance...there's a mini city there with almost everything you could need! So helpful, even a bank and component vendors there :P<br>
